<headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 28 at 7:16PM EDT  by NWS Tallahassee</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of Berrien County
through 745 PM EDT...
At 716 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Alapaha, or 7 miles west of Willacoochee, moving west at 20 mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.
Locations impacted include...
Nashville, Enigma, Alapaha, Berrien Co A/P, Weber, Glory and
Bannockburn.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.00 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>This storm may intensify, so be certain to monitor local radio
stations and available television stations for additional information
and possible warnings from the National Weather Service.</instruction>
